      • acknowledged

        public void acknowledged(EventBatch events)
        Description copied from interface: ConnectionCallbacks
        Will be called once for each EventBatch that is acknowledged (has been replicated amongst Splunk Indexers). Events sent via Connection.send are internally batched (even if their is only one Event in an EventBatch), which is why acknowledgments are per-EventBatch and not per-Event.
        Specified by:
        acknowledged in interface ConnectionCallbacks

      • addCheckpointer

        public void addCheckpointer(String sequenceNumber,
                            com.amazonaws.services.kinesis.clientlibrary.interfaces.IRecordProcessorCheckpointer checkpointer)
        Stores a checkpointer function associated with a given sequence number so that the callback can call the right checkpointer function when the batch is acknowledged by Splunk. Should be called right before sending an event batch to Splunk.
        Parameters:
        sequenceNumber - the highest (last) sequence number in the event batch to be sent
        checkpointer - the checkpointer function passed to ProcessRecords
